str2: From, away from. A primary particle; 'off, ' i.e. Away, in various senses.
From ageiro; properly, the town-square; by implication, a market or thoroughfare.

str2: Strengthened for a primary edo; used only in certain tenses, the rest being supplied by phago; to eat.
If. From ei and an; a conditional particle; in case that, provided, etc.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Middle - 3rd Person Plural
str2: Lit: I dip, submerge, but specifically of ceremonial dipping; I baptize.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
Other, another (of more than two), different. A primary word; 'else, ' i.e. Different.

str2: From para and lambano; to receive near, i.e. Associate with oneself; by analogy, to assume an office; figuratively, to learn.
From kratos; to use strength, i.e. Seize or retain.
Dipping, washing (of a ceremonial character). From baptizo; ablution.
A drinking cup, the contents of the cup; fig: the portion which God allots.
As if from xeo (of friction) to boil or heat); a vessel, i.e., a measure for liquids or solids.
A bronze vessel, brazen utensil. Diminutive from chalkos; a copper dish.
A couch, bed, portable bed or mat, a couch for reclining at meals, possibly also a bier. From klino; a couch.
